text: Adam Ashburnham was an English MP in the 16th century,The Visitations of the County of Sussex Made and Taken in the Years 1530, Thomas Benolte, John Philipot, George Owen, Harleian Society, London, 1905 and represented Winchelsea from 1593 to 1597.History of Parliament on-line His grandson was Sir Denny Ashburnham, 1st Baronet, Member of Parliament for Hastings from 1660 to 1689. ==References== Category:English MPs 1593
title: Adam Ashburnham
